-- SE Asia Stocks-Firmer; Thai shares rise to 3-month high ahead of rate decision
-- 
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 07:30AM EDT
-- None



March 11 (Reuters) - Thai stocks rose on Tuesday to a three-month high ahead of a monetary policy decision by Thailand's central bank while other Southeast Asian markets recovered after most of them eased in the previous session due to weak Chinese export data.

The day's trading was strong in volume, but gains were capped by concerns about sluggish economic growth in China and continued tensions over Ukraine. Thailand's main index <.SETI> ended 1.1 percent firmer at its highest close since Dec. 11 on hopes the central bank would cut its benchmark interest rate by 25 basis points on Wednesday to help the economy cope with damage from months of political unrest. The stock market, which saw a foreign funds inflow of $7.77 million on Tuesday, may gain further as Thailand is expected to lift a state of emergency in capital Bangkok due to pressure from businesses and in the light of improving security. [ID:nL3N0M81BM] Morgan Stanley, after the market closed on Tuesday, downgraded Thailand to "underweight" from "equalweight," citing sluggish economic growth and prolonged political instability. Philippine shares <.PSI> closed 0.7 percent higher, with foreign investors buying a net $30.7 million worth, while Malaysia <.KLSE> gained 0.4 percent, with $22.1 million foreign inflows. Singapore's benchmark Straits Times index <.FTSTI> ended 0.1 percent up after touching a near two-month high in early trade. The Jakarta Composite Index <.JKSE> ended 0.6 firmer at a near eight-month closing high, despite foreign investors selling a net $9.27 million in shares. Vietnam's benchmark VN Index <.VNI> ended up 0.8 percent, its fifth consecutive gain. For Asian Companies click; [nTOPEQA]   For South East Asia Hot Stock reports, click; [.SI] [.KL] [.BK]  SOUTHEAST ASIAN STOCK MARKETS  Change on day  Market Current Prev ClosePct Move  TR SE Asia Index*   404.62402.38   +0.56  Singapore  3129.40   3126.63   +0.09  Kuala Lumpur   1828.55   1822.06   +0.36  Bangkok1364.28   1349.05   +1.13  Jakarta4704.21   4677.25   +0.58  Manila 6529.58   6487.23   +0.65  Ho Chi Minh 588.50583.69   +0.82Change on year  Market Current   End 2013Pct Move  TR SE Asia Index*   404.62388.37   +4.18  Singapore  3129.40   3167.43   -1.20  Kuala Lumpur   1828.55   1866.96 